CMake-SDL2-OpenGL-Imgui Example

Linux Instructions (Ubuntu 20:04 LTS):

Ensure the following packages/third-party libraries from the Standard and
Universe Repositories are also installed:

- libopengl-dev (1.3.2-1~ubuntu0.20.04.2+)
- libglm-dev (0.9.9.7+ds-1+).
- libglew-dev (2.1.0-4+)
- libsdl2-dev (2.0.10+dfsg1-3+)

Then make sure the following header libraries are included and linked (the
default location to install them are in subdirectories in the inc folder):

- imgui https://github.com/ocornut/imgui/

Load into VSCode and use the CMakeTools to run CMake/Build or CMake/Run tasks

Additional support tools useful for development:

- Build EAR https://github.com/rizsotto/Bear

Note that to compile  requires a compiler with C++20 support such as
gcc 10.3.

